---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Research · Deep Pearl AI"
  description="The Deep Pearl AI research agenda: perception and 3D, representation learning, reasoning and symbol, agents and control, and scaling."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <a class="back" href="/">
        <span aria-hidden="true">&larr;</span>
        <span>Deep Pearl AI</span>
      </a>
      <p class="eyebrow"><span class="bar" aria-hidden="true"></span>Research</p>
      <h1>The research agenda</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        The lines of work the lab is studying and building, from how machines
        perceive the 3D world to how they reason, act, and scale. Everything
        here feeds back into Multivac, Multivac Physics, ALEX-1, and EMOTE4D.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="now-band">
        <p class="label">Currently learning</p>
        <ul class="pill-list">
          <li>representation learning</li>
          <li>interpretability</li>
          <li>adaptive computation</li>
          <li>edge deployment</li>
          <li>robotic integration</li>
          <li>perception and 3D</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="research-groups">
        <section class="research-group" aria-labelledby="g-3d">
          <h2 id="g-3d">Perception and 3D</h2>
          <p class="group-note">How machines recover and edit the structure of the physical world.</p>
          <ul class="research-list">
            <li><strong>3D reconstruction</strong> — single image to 3D, stereo vision</li>
            <li><strong>NeRF plus diffusion</strong> for 3D generation and scene editing</li>
            <li><strong>Articulated human and garment modeling</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Gaussian splatting</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="research-group" aria-labelledby="g-rep">
          <h2 id="g-rep">Representation and learning</h2>
          <p class="group-note">What models learn, and whether the brain offers a better recipe.</p>
          <ul class="research-list">
            <li><strong>Self-supervised learning</strong> — JEPA-style predictive learning</li>
            <li><strong>Vision Transformers</strong>, DINOv2</li>
            <li><strong>Brain-to-model alignment</strong> — retinal neural coding, brain-optimized networks</li>
            <li><strong>Non-backprop and brain-inspired learning</strong> — Hebbian, predictive coding, forward-forward, equilibrium propagation</li>
            <li><strong>KAN-style minimal networks</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="research-group" aria-labelledby="g-sym">
          <h2 id="g-sym">Reasoning and symbol</h2>
          <p class="group-note">Where pattern-matching ends and genuine reasoning begins.</p>
          <ul class="research-list">
            <li><strong>Mathematical cognition</strong> — symbolic math, symbolic regression</li>
            <li><strong>Mechanistic interpretability</strong> — math transformer circuits</li>
            <li><strong>Neural-symbolic hybrid systems</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Word models to world models</strong> — the probabilistic language of thought line</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="research-group" aria-labelledby="g-agents">
          <h2 id="g-agents">Agents and control</h2>
          <p class="group-note">From tool use to embodied skill — how systems decide and act.</p>
          <ul class="research-list">
            <li><strong>Tool-using and agentic LLMs</strong> — ReAct, Toolformer, Voyager, generative agents</li>
            <li><strong>Task decomposition</strong> — hierarchical planning, HTN</li>
            <li><strong>Hierarchical RL</strong> — options, skill discovery</li>
            <li><strong>Generalist and embodied robotic agents</strong> — Gato, RoboCat</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="research-group span-2" aria-labelledby="g-scale">
          <h2 id="g-scale">Scaling</h2>
          <p class="group-note">Doing more with the compute you have, and measuring what the compute bought.</p>
          <ul class="research-list">
            <li><strong>Mixture of experts</strong> — dynamic routing, sparsity</li>
            <li><strong>Scientific reasoning evaluation</strong> — SciBench</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="callout">
        <p>
          <strong>Applied, not abstract.</strong> Evaluation findings shape what
          Multivac and Multivac Physics test next. Representation and edge work
          flows into ALEX-1 and EMOTE4D. The research agenda exists to make the
          ventures sharper — and the ventures keep the research honest.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="influences">
        <p class="label">Influences</p>
        <p>
          World model and edge AI research by the author of
          <a href="https://github.com/yuedajiong" rel="noopener">github.com/yuedajiong</a>.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
